The results showed that detectable antibodies to IBV antigen in chickens reached the peak 14 days after the booster inoculation, Specific antibodies increased significantly in the chickens from Groups 2, 3, 5 and 7, which were much more than that of Group 4 or Group 6. The results also indicated that Group 2 had been able to elicit higher specific antibodies against IBV, compared to Group 1 (P
 < 0.05) after booster. Control chickens in Group 8 which were injected with PBS repeatedly did not show detectable specific antibodies (Fig. 5
).
